<p>Thousands of mourners and dignitaries gathered as Kenya’s long-time opposition figure Raila Odinga was laid to rest on Sunday in Bondo, western Kenya, following an Anglican service; the burial proceeded without major incident under a heavy security presence at his rural home [reuters.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1]. His death on Wednesday in India at age 80, where he had been receiving medical treatment, prompted days of nationwide tributes and grief [reuters.com#1][bbc.com#1]. Earlier memorial events were marred by tragedy, with at least five deaths and hundreds of injuries amid crowd surges during viewings and ceremonies in Nairobi and elsewhere [reuters.com#1][aljazeera.com#1][dw.com#1]. Former U.S. President Barack Obama posted a tribute calling Odinga a champion of peace [reuters.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/CetbG3CrL7HehzuwzI5bePwYJ5N75DgBl8d30GVGKyx9mcWt0HMprzdpCIOI1EPTdr1qfDlbUyjSCmBNTHmPxifHch1tuOavVVYy_x1p' alt='Mourners gather at Jomo Kenyatta Stadium in Mamboleo during Raila Odinga’s funeral events.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Crowd management: Authorities canceled a planned procession in Kisumu and airlifted the coffin to the city stadium to reduce risk, with a medical source reporting 74 people treated mainly for fainting and dehydration [dawn.com#1].</li><li>Military honors: After the main service, the cortege proceeded to a private interment accompanied by a military band gun salute [reuters.com#1].</li><li>State funeral day: President William Ruto led a state funeral on Friday in Nairobi, where a stampede among mourners caused further casualties and injuries [dawn.com#1][aljazeera.com#1][dw.com#1].</li><li>Thursday incident: Security forces opened fire to disperse a surging crowd during a lying-in-state in Nairobi on Thursday, resulting in multiple fatalities [dawn.com#1][dw.com#1].</li><li>Security presence: The final interment at Odinga’s rural home took place under heavy security, with large crowds gathering peacefully nearby [abcnews.go.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>Without Baba, we are dead. We don’t have anywhere to go - Don Pelido, supporter</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Barack Obama: Praised Odinga as a champion of peace and someone who put country above politics. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/thousands-turn-out-funeral-kenyan-opposition-leader-after-deadly-week-2025-10-19/'>Reuters</a>)</li><li>Raila Odinga Jr.: Expressed relief and closure for the family as his father was brought home for burial. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/thousands-turn-out-funeral-kenyan-opposition-leader-after-deadly-week-2025-10-19/'>Reuters</a>)</li><li>Medical staff in Kisumu: Said crowd behavior improved and airlifting the body prevented bigger problems on the roads. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1949823/huge-turnout-as-body-of-revered-kenya-politician-odinga-heads-home'>Dawn</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/thousands-turn-out-funeral-kenyan-opposition-leader-after-deadly-week-2025-10-19/'>Thousands turn out for funeral of Kenyan opposition leader after deadly week</a> - reuters.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1949823/huge-turnout-as-body-of-revered-kenya-politician-odinga-heads-home'>Huge turnout as body of revered Kenya politician Odinga heads home</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cgjd6j3j099o'>Ex-Kenyan leader Raila Odinga buried after days of memorial events</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/final-interment-kenyas-former-prime-minister-odinga-underway-126656983'>Final interment for Kenya&#x27;s former prime minister Odinga underway</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/19/kenyas-revered-opposition-leader-raila-odinga-being-laid-to-rest'>Kenya’s revered opposition leader Raila Odinga laid to rest</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/kenya-bids-final-farewell-to-raila-odinga/a-74417254'>Kenya bids final farewell to Raila Odinga</a> - dw.com</li></ul>